title: For Sale:  For sale: AR 15 (pics added)
postcontent: Thanks for looking! For sale, nearly brand new AR 15. Had only had about 300 rds down range, without a single hiccup. Upper is a Palmetto State 16" midlength, with a Melonited barrel and a military standard 1/7 twist (will shoot a full range of ammunition, from 55 gr to the heavier 77 gr Mk 262 OTM loads). The 7075-T6 forged aluminum upper receiver has a milspec black hard coat anodized finish and is T-marked. The front sight is a standard "F"-marked sight block, and the front handguards are standard milspec for the midlength gas system. BCG is nitrided Davidson Defense.  Rear sight is a UTG Pro flip up BUIS. Lower is Anderson 7075-T6 forged with the standard milspec hard coat anodized finish as well. A DPMS lower parts kit was used to complete this rifle. If you're not familiar with the melonite (sometimes called nitrided, black nitride or QPQ) treatment, this process is superior to phosphate coating, stainless steel AND/OR chrome lining. Depending on the manufacturer, a chrome lining might have irregularities in thickness that can immediately affect accuracy. Even in time, the chrome lining can wear away, once again affecting accuracy. Phosphate and stainless untreated barrels will wear, over time. Again, accuracy is compromised. Melonite is not a finish, but an actual treatment that increases both the hardness and the life of the barrel. The Melonite process leaves the barrel with a smooth and deep black color. The rifle currently has a OD GREEN buttstock installed, as I did not have a black milspec one present, at the time. Price is the same for either one, but the black one won't be available until 19 or 20, September. Pics will be added soon. Price is $650 firm, and it includes two milspec aluminum 30 rd magazines. (Not interested in trades; cash only.) Feel free to contact me for any questions.
